Dr. Ed Montgomery, President Obama's Director of Recovery for Auto Communities and Workers, will be visiting Michigan on May 7th and 8th, 2009. He will be accompanied by representatives from government agencies to meet with workers, local officials, and community leaders in Grand Rapids, Flint, and Warren. The purpose of the visit is to discuss ways to support and revitalize the auto industry workers and communities that have been heavily impacted during these challenging times. The group will also explore how to ensure that the federal government's resources are reaching those who need them the most.